Source: libutf8
Section: libs
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Warren MacEvoy <wmacevoy@gmail.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13)
Standards-Version: 4.6.0
Homepage: https://github.com/wmacevoy/utf8

Package: libutf8-1
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Small permissive UTF-8 encode/decode library
 Encodes and decodes sequences of unsigned 32-bit integers to and from
 a UTF-8-style byte stream. Supports 1 through 6 byte sequences (up to
 31-bit values). Decoding is permissive: invalid bytes are passed through
 as their raw value.

Package: libutf8-dev
Section: libdevel
Architecture: any
Depends: libutf8-1 (= ${binary:Version}), ${misc:Depends}
Description: Small permissive UTF-8 encode/decode library (development files)
 Encodes and decodes sequences of unsigned 32-bit integers to and from
 a UTF-8-style byte stream. Supports 1 through 6 byte sequences (up to
 31-bit values). Decoding is permissive: invalid bytes are passed through
 as their raw value.
 .
 This package contains the header files and static library for development.
